If the resident still refuses to participate in any aspect of the resident's individual treatment plan, the ICF/ID may petition the District Court for a de novo determination of the appropriateness of the proposed treatment. Within seven (7) days, the court shall conduct a hearing, consistent with the resident's rights to due process of law, and shall utilize the following factors in reaching its determination:
Whether the treatment is necessary to protect other residents or the resident himself from harm;
Whether the resident is incapable of giving informed consent to the proposed treatment;
Whether any less restrictive alternative treatment exists; and
Whether the proposed treatment carries any significant risk of permanent side effects.
